<blockquote>
<center>
<b>The Week in Review</b><br>
<i>The last week's columns</i>


</center><p>
<a href="/thcc/content/feder/fede010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/feder.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="DON FEDER">
<b>AIR GUNS, INFANTICIDE AND ABORTION'S DEMENTED DOGMA</b></a><br>Last week, a Canadian court dismissed charges against an Ontario woman who chose to exercise control
     of her body by putting a pellet from an air gun in the brain of her unborn child. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/fields/fiel010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/fields.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="SUZANNE FIELDS">
<b>AN EBONICS PLAGUE ON RACE RELATIONS</b></a><br>Ebonics has not been helpful to race relations. It brings out the worst thoughts if not the worst
     words from both black and white. Whites who defend ebonics as a second language, or even a place for
     it in the classroom, sound patronizing and condescending. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/greenberg/gree010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/greenberg.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Paul Greenberg">
<b>EBONICS</b></a><br>Today's lesson: You dis somebody's language, you be in trouble. 
 
         This caveat needs to be kept in mind as a national debate with a lot more heat than light erupts out
     of Oakland, Calif., where a school board seeking the usual federal grant set out to get one for the study of
     something called Ebonics.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/novak/nova010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/novak.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="ROBERT NOVAK">
<b>INSIDE REPORT</b></a><br>Rep. Linda Smith, who clashed with Newt Gingrich over campaign finance reform as
     a freshman Republican in the 104th Congress, could end up voting against his re-election as speaker of
     the House.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/snow/snow010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/snow.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="TONY SNOW">
<b>THE SEARCH FOR TRUTH</b></a><br>Scandal has crept upon the U.S. Capitol on little cat's feet. The "mindless
     cannibalism" Jim Wright prophesied nearly eight years ago has arrived: Democrats are turning
     Gingrich-bashing into an Olympic sport, and Republicans are preparing to conduct Torquemada-like
     inquisitions of Richard Gephardt, David Bonior, Bill Clinton, Hillary Rodham Clinton and anybody who
     has purchased so much as a frozen yogurt in the state of Arkansas. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/bozell/boze010397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/bozell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="L. BRENT BOZELL">
<b>EXIT BRYANT GUMBEL, UNPROFESSIONAL JOURNALIST</b></a><br>

Pop the champagne corks: The 15-year tenure of arrogant liberal Bryant Gumbel
     as host of NBC's "Today" show is over.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/chapman/chap010397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/chapman.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="STEPHEN CHAPMAN">
<b>THE DRUG WARRIORS VS. MEDICAL MARIJUANA</b></a><br>

Federal drug czar Barry McCaffrey appeared at a news conference Monday to
     proclaim his "absolute trust in the judgment of the American people." He did this
     in the middle of a tantrum over two ballot initiatives approved by the people of
     California and Arizona, who last time I checked were still Americans.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/novak/nova010397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/novak.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="ROBERT D. NOVAK">
<b>BUILDING NEWT'S LYNCH MOB</b></a><br>

Nothing in the assault on Newt Gingrich is more
     preposterous than the claim that he diverted funds from poor, hungry children to
     his scheme for a right-wing America.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/snow/snow010397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/snow.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="TONY SNOW">
<b>BONIER V. GINGRICH</b></a><br>

David Bonior's crusade against Newt Gingrich has battered
     the speaker and splintered Republicans. Yet, few people realize it threatens to
     inflict even heavier damage on Democrats.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/sowell/sowe010397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/sowell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="THOMAS SOWELL">
<b>BRAINWASHING CONTINUES</b></a><br>

During a recent visit to Australia, a friend told me that he is going into debt to pay
     for private schooling for his children -- mainly to keep them away from the
     counter-cultural brainwashing that goes on in the public schools there. Of course,
     the same things go on in the public schools here.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/tyrrell/tyrr010397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/tyrrell.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="R. EMMETT TYRRELL JR.">
<b>PUBLIC NUISANCES</b></a><br>

The most serious task facing American politics has moved beyond ministering to
     the material needs of the citizenry. In that pursuit, our government has failed
     spectacularly.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/bozell/boze010297.html"><img src="/thcc/images/bozell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="L. BRENT BOZELL">
<b>HOLLYWOOD'S WINNERS AND LOSERS, 1996</b></a><br>

Perhaps no industry is more happy to see 1996 come to an end than Hollywood. From
     start to finish, the year found the entertainment world embroiled in one controversy after
     another, under assault for its negative impact on the cultural well-being.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/feder/fede010297.html"><img src="/thcc/images/feder.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="DON FEDER">
<b>PAUKEN WOULD TAKE TEXAS TRIUMPH NATIONAL</b></a><br>

The chairmanship of the Republican National Committee usually goes to one of the
     party's movers and shakers -- power brokers who are shaky on principles and primarily
     concerned with the forward movement of their careers.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/huffington/huff010297.html"><img src="/thcc/images/huffington.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="HUFFINGTON">
<b>A BREAK IN THE RANKS</b></a><br>

"We have seen no
     erosion whatsoever," House Majority Whip Tom DeLay said on "Meet the Press"
     Sunday, echoing Majority Leader Dick Armey, who has been predicting with "no doubt"
     that all 227 Republican members will vote for the speaker.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/saunders/saun010297.html"><img src="/thcc/images/saunders.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="DEBRA J. SAUNDERS">
<b>THE NEWTSTER IS SOUNDING LIKE HILLARY</b></a><br>


     "He screwed up, and he's admitted it," House Budget Committee Chairman John Kasich
     told ABC News' "This Week" -- obviously referring to Speaker Newt Gingrich and his
     acknowledgment that he provided the House Ethics Committee with false information. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/sowell/sowe010297.html"><img src="/thcc/images/sowell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="THOMAS SOWELL">
<b>THE FEDERALIST PAPERS REVISITED</b></a><br>

One of the small but hopeful changes that will come in with the New Year is a California
     law requiring high schools to include "The Federalist Papers" among their assigned
     readings. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/bowles/bowl123196.html"><img src="/thcc/images/bowles.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="LINDA BOWLES">
<b>NEW YEARS RESOLUTIONS</b></a><br>We are once again at that time of the year when it is customary to confess our shortcomings and formulate our resolutions for
     overcoming them. In that spirit, I must confess to having written bad things about various liberal heroes and icons.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/huffington/huff123196.html"><img src="/thcc/images/huffington.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="ARIANNA HUFFINGTON">
<b>POLITICS 1996: A BRIDGE TOO FAR</b></a><br>It's time for one last look at 1996 before we say goodbye -- a few final words (promise!) on the woeful political year behind
     us. And then a quick peek at 1997.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/murchison/murc123196.html"><img src="/thcc/images/murchison.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="WILLIAM MURCHISON">
<b>MAIN STREET U.S.A.</b></a><br>You bet the "ebonics" fuss -- still buzzing in our ears, thanks to the usual late-December news dearth -- is about race. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/chapman/chap123096.html"><img src="/thcc/images/chapman.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="STEPHEN CHAPMAN">
<b>ARE IMMIGRANTS DESTROYING THE "COMMON CULTURE"?</b></a><br>A few weeks ago, two Iraqi refugees married a pair of sisters from Lincoln, Neb. Shortly afterward, the men found themselves in jail. Why? Because the girls were only 13 and 14
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/feder/fede123096.html"><img src="/thcc/images/feder.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="DON FEDER">
<b>UNACCEPTABLE PEOPLE AWARDS FOR 1996</b></a><br>Given the number of political pests and celebrity geeks cluttering the landscape, choosing my annual Unacceptable People Awards is always a challenge.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/fields/fiel123096.html"><img src="/thcc/images/fields.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Suzanne Fields">
<b>LOSING IT AT THE MOVIES</b></a><br>Hollywood's obsession with violence and sex is well known, but maybe we ought to start paying attention to the ways certain movies twist sensibilities, not only making mush of moral issues, but depriving the audience of the slightest sense of thoughtful complexity and aesthetic cohesion. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/greenberg/gree123096.html"><img src="/thcc/images/greenberg.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Paul Greenberg">
<b>NEWT GINGRICH FESSES UP -- AND IS PROMPTLY REWARDED</b></a><br>Plea bargaining, the bane of the American criminal justice system, is well on its way to becoming enshrined in the U.S. Congress, too. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/novak/nova123096.html"><img src="/thcc/images/novak.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="ROBERT D. NOVAK">
<b>POST-GINGRICH POLITICS</b></a><br> Behind the solid Republican front supporting the retention of Newt Gingrich as House speaker, the staffs of two potentially rival Texans -- Majority Leader Dick Armey and Majority Whip Tom DeLay -- have been maneuvering for the possible Republican succession. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/saunders/saun123096.html"><img src="/thcc/images/saunders.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="DEBRA J. SAUNDERS">
<b>EAT THESE EDUISMS</b></a><br>Whenever you hear educrats pronounce the following eduisms, know that your children are in danger: When we say that Ebonics is genetically based, we are using "genetic" as a synonym for genesis.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/snow/snow123096.html"><img src="/thcc/images/snow.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="TONY SNOW">
<b>GINGRICH</b></a><br>Newt Gingrich, reaching out to conservative pundits, called me the day before Christmas. We chatted at length two days later.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/williams/will123096.html"><img src="/thcc/images/williams.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Armstrong Williams">
<b>DECLINE OF A NATION</b></a><br>An inherent paradox in the cyclical rise and decline of nations is that the prosperity brought about by the labors of a good and free people is often the undoing of their virtue, their freedom and, finally, their nation.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/bozell/boze122796.html"><img src="/thcc/images/bozell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="L. Brent Bozell">
<b>WHITE HOUSE ADULTERY? NOBODY IN THE PRESS WANTS TO KNOW</b></a><br>Long-time Friend-of-Bill David Watkins has told a tale no one wants to hear. No one in the establishment media, that is.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/chapman/chap122796.html"><img src="/thcc/images/chapman.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="STEPHEN CHAPMAN">
<b>IN 1996, A BEAR MARKET FOR TYRANTS</b></a><br>Does the Endangered Species Act have any room for people on the verge of extinction? If so, the Environmental Protection Agency should move to prevent the disappearance of the world's dictators, who have gotten as scarce as snail darters.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/greenberg/gree122796.html"><img src="/thcc/images/greenberg.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Paul Greenberg">
<b>THE ELECTORAL COLLEGE</b></a><br>It happens every four years. In each of the 50 states, a small group of people whose names are soon forgotten comes together and ... elects the next president of the United States. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/huffington/huff122796.html"><img src="/thcc/images/huffington.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="ARIANNA HUFFINGTON">
<b>THE GINGRICH LEADERSHIP: IS IT ACT I OR ACT V?</b></a><br>The answer to the question "Will Newt Gingrich survive?" depends on whether we are in Act I or in Act V of this particular play.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/murchison/murc122796.html"><img src="/thcc/images/murchison.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="WILLIAM MURCHISON">
<b>MAIN STREET U.S.A.</b></a><br>Polls -- don't stop reading, please! -- continue to shed Christmas joy. Americans, we learn in this electoral season, regard government with the same flinty-eyed scorn they normally reserve for telephone solicitors at dinnertime.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/novak/nova122796.html"><img src="/thcc/images/novak.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Robert Novak">
<b>INSIDE REPORT</b></a><br>Hours after President Clinton said on Dec. 13 that Israeli settlements were "absolutely" an obstacle to peace, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu sought an invitation to the White House. He was turned down.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/saunders/saun122796.html"><img src="/thcc/images/saunders.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="DEBRA J. SAUNDERS">
<b>OAKLAND'S EBONICS FARCE</b></a><br>A bright 6-year-old in my neighborhood speaks black dialect. A few times, he has run up to me to tell me he is excited about something, but I couldn't understand him.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/sowell/sowe122796.html"><img src="/thcc/images/sowell.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="THOMAS SOWELL">
<b>FROM MARXISM TO THE MARKET</b></a><br>Recently a student wrote to ask me a familiar question: How and why had I changed from a young leftist to someone with my present views, which are essentially in favor of free markets and traditional values?
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/tyrrell/tyrr122796.html"><img src="/thcc/images/tyrrell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="R. EMMETT TYRRELL JR.">
<b>PUBLIC NUISANCES</b></a><br> Last week, there must have been moments when House Speaker Newt Gingrich wished that he simply did not exist.
<p><br>




</blockquote>









