Subject: C-NEWS: INTERNET GUILD MEETS (You're invited!)<P>

    Please forward this message -- help distribute it widely -- to your e-mail
list, on your bulletin board (in both senses of the term), etc.<BR>
    We have made a tremendous effort to ensure that everyone who wants to be
on this list is on it, and everyone who doesn't isn't.  If we've left you on
by mistake, just let us know (see the note at the end).<BR>

    If you're not in or near the Washington, DC area, please pass this along
to someone who is, and see the note at the end.<P>

*******************************************<P>

INTERNET GUILD (DC chapter) MEETS!<BR>
The Washington, D.C. chapter of the Internet Guild [a nonprofit,
public-interest organization of conservative, libertarian, and free-market
activists online -- <A HREF="http://www.axsamer.org/~iguild">http://www.axsamer.org/~iguild</A>] announces<P>
        >>> its Regular Last Tuesday of the Month Dinner.<P>

IG members, prospective members, friends and guests will gather to discuss
politics and the Internet and to network with other computer-literate (or
- -semiliterate) people active in the fight against Big Government.  Steve
Allen will discuss the INTERNET POLITICAL REPORT and the reviews it has
received.  ("Two thumbs up!" "A masterpiece!" "Do not give away the stunning
surprise!"  Oh, sorry, those are the reviews for _The Crying Game_.)<P>

You're invited!  Tell your friends! Bring a guest! Bring lots of guests!
Bring your family, your co-workers, people you ride the Metro with!  <P>

