<body>
<title>Phil Brennan --Mephistopheles For President
        </title>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" background="/townhall/background.jpg">
<blockquote><blockquote>

<center>
<h3> Mephistopheles For President 
</h3>
</center>
<p>
<hr size=3 width=30%>
<i>
By Phil Brennan
<br>Editor and Publisher
<br> <a href="http://www.pacg.com/pvbr/">Wednesday On The Web</a>
</i>
<p>
<br><center><h4>Americans appear to be getting ready to sign a compact with Satan.</h4></center>
<p>On the <i>McLaughlin Group</i> the other night Fred Barnes described the voters' seeming 
willingness to overlook Slick Willie's sleazy character because they think he's good at 
providing bread and circuses &quot;a Faustian bargain.&quot; </p>
<p>Host McLaughlin explained for the less literate viewers in his audience that Barnes was 
referring to Dr. Faust's sale of his soul to Mephistopheles, who McLaughlin identified as 
the devil. </p>
<p>When you think about it, it's a hell of a good metaphor for what the voters are about to do 
next Tuesday (unless there's a mass outbreak of sanity and a sudden epidemic of virtue). </p>
<p>In return for America's soul, the Mephistophilean <font color="#FF0000">Clinton</font> promises the world. So who 
cares if he's got horns and cloven hooves? It's expansive government programs that 
count, and Bob Dole wants to get rid of all that federal largesse. Better to stick with the 
devil you know than the angel you don't know. </p>
<p>To mix literary illusions, Clinton is seen as the beneficent statesman who delivers 
sleighfulls of goodies to the ordinary people while Dole comes across as a Scrooge who'd 
take the crutches away from poor Tiny Tim, deny him needed medical care, and throw the 
whole Cratchet family out into the street to fend for themselves. </p>
<p>In selling their souls to the devil in return for his bribes, the voters are forgetting that they 
will someday be called upon to pay the devil his due, much as the German people who sold 
their souls to Adolf Hitler for autobahns and Volkswagens and a booming economy paid 
first with their freedom and then amid the ashes and rubble of crushing defeat in World 
War II. </p>
<p>They may think that life under a re-elected Clinton will be Heaven. They will learn in time 
that it was really Hell. </p>
<p>The pro-Clinton media openly admits, in their own words, that Slick Willie is no angel. But 
they won't take the next step, which is to identify him for what he <i>is</i> -- evil personified. </p>
</blockquote></blockquote>      
<p>
<br>
<br>
<center>
<a href="/townhall/tbut.map"><img src="/townhall/tbut.gif" ismap border="0"></a>
</center>

</body>
