<html>

<title>FRC's Hot List of Links</title>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000">

<center>
<a href="/townhall/FRC/images/topban.map">
<img src="/townhall/FRC/images/topban.gif" ismap border="0"></a>
<img src = "/townhall/FRC/hotlist/hotlist.gif"></center>
<br>
<center><h4>(This page was last updated on 12/16/96.)</h4></center>

<p><font size=4><i>
Below we have provided an assortment of links for your benefit 
and enjoyment. For now, we have divided these links into 3 different 
sections:</i> <a href="#govt">Government-Related Links</a>, 
<a href="#policy">Public Policy Groups</a> <i>and various</i> 
<a href="#religious">Religious Links</a>. <i>These links will change 
frequently, so be sure to check back often.
<p>
In the future we plan on adding other lists that will help you 
to research various topics that FRC covers in more detail or topics 
that we don't cover at all.
</i><p>
<b>PLEASE NOTE:</b> <i>FRC does not necessarily endorse or promote any of 
the organizations, subjects or ideas provided by these links. They are 
merely tools for your own benefit.</i></font>

<p><hr size=3><p>

<a name="govt">
<center><b><font size=5><font size=6>G</font>OVERNMENT-<font size=6>R</font>ELATED 
<font size=6>L</font>INKS</font></b></center>

<p><dl>

<dt><a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/WH/Welcome.html"><font size=+2>The 
White House</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains information about the President, Vice President, their 
E-Mail addresses and their families. It also contains &quot;White House 
History and Tours&quot;, the latest press releases, State of the Union 
Addresses, White House documents and speeches, etc. It also has links to 
other government services.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.house.gov/"><font size=+2>The U.S. House of 
Representatives</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains information about all of the current and past 
legislation pertaining to the 104th Congress. It contains the full text 
of bills and amendments, the current status of legislation that is being 
debated, and it even shows how individual members voted on specific 
measures. It also contains names, addresses, phone numbers and E-Mail 
addresses for each member.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.senate.gov/"><font size=+2>The U.S. Senate</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains a directory of all the senators by name and state. A 
photo, address, phone number and short biography of each senator is included. 
If available, E-Mail addresses are given as well. If you wish, you can take a 
&quot;virtual tour&quot; of the Capitol building. A brief history of the 
Senate is also available.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://thomas.loc.gov/"><font size=+2>Thomas Legislative 
Information on the Internet</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains the full text of all the legislation from the 
103rd and 104th Congress. It also contains information about all of the 
current legislation being debated. It contains the full text of the U.S. 
Constitution and an explanation as of how our laws are made. It also 
contains links to other government branches.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.loc.gov/"><font size=+2>The Library of Congress</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains general information about the Library, and it allows 
you to view major exhibits and gives you information about upcoming Library 
events. It even has &quot;Digital Library Collections&quot; - images from 
different historical collections.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.ustreas.gov/"><font size=+2>The Department of the 
Treasury</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains everything from photographs and biographical information 
on Treasury Officers to Secretary of the Treasury speeches, press releases 
and a &quot;short cut to IRS Tax forms&quot;. It also has a link to each of the 
12 Treasury bureaus, including the IRS, the U.S. Customs Service, the U.S. Mint, 
and others.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.gov.mci.net/fed/jud/jud.html"><font size=+2>Judicial 
Branch</font></a>
<dd><b>This web page contains pictures and biographies of all of the supreme 
court justices.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.army.mil"><font size=+2>The U.S. Army Homepage</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains a photo and biography about the chief of staff, 
the Army mission and vision, and recruiting information. You can take a 
&quot;tour&quot; of the Army, and for more information this site provides 
over 300 links to other Army or Army-related homepages.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.usmc.mil/"><font size=+2>The U.S. Marine 
Corps</font></a>
<dd><b>Here you have access to all kinds of information about the Marines, 
including their mission, their history, links to other marine sites, and  
a place where you can write to Marines in Bosnia. They also give more detail  
about the mission in Bosnia.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.ncts.navy.mil/navpalib/.www/welcome.html"><font size=+2>The Navy</font></a>
<dd><b>All of the information you need to know about the Navy is contained 
in this site. It tells you the current status of the Navy which is updated 
weekly, it has fact sheets on the various Navy aircraft and ships, answers 
to frequently asked questions about the Navy, and even a digital imagery 
section.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.af.mil"><font size=+2>The U.S. Air Force</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains current news and information about the Air Force. It 
has biographies of Air Force leaders, pictures of the people, operations 
and weapon systems, and links to other Air Force Web Servers. It even has 
the latest news about what's going on with the Air Force in Bosnia, 
including sound clips.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.dot.gov/dotinfo/uscg/"><font size=+2>The U.S. Coast 
Guard</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains all kinds of information about the Coast Guard, 
including recruiting information, aircraft and boat information, navigation 
information, communications information, etc.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.dtic.dla.mil/defenselink/"><font size=+2>The 
Department of Defense</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains news releases, facts, photos, and information about 
the people behind the DOD. It also has links to other DOD agencies.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.si.edu/"><font size=+2>The Smithsonian 
Institution</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains a myriad of information about the Smithsonian 
and its many museums. It contains an overview of all the Smithsonian 
Museums, information on new and temporary exhibitions, a directory of 
the staff, and even a shopping mall.</b>

</dl>

<p><hr size=3><p>

<a name="policy">
<center><b><font size=5><font size=6>P</font>UBLIC 
<font size=6>P</font>OLICY/<font size=6>P</font>OLITICAL 
<font size=6>G</font>ROUPS</font></b></center>

<p><dl>

<dt><a href="http://www.policy.com"><font size=+2>Policy Street</font></a>
<dd><b>Policy Street connects you with over 100 of the world's premier 
think tanks, advocacy groups and other public policy analysis 
organizations. Explore the variety of views presented by Policy Street 
groups, and endorse or challenge their views.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.politicsnow.com"><font size=+2>Politics Now</font></a>
<dd><b>This site will keep you up to date on the Presidential 
campaign and the issues that will play a big part is this year's election. 
It contains a multimedia archive of all of the speeches from the Republican 
National Convention, and they even have a political trivia game.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.cgx.com"><font size=+2>Conservative Generation 
X</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains information for, about and by the Conservative 
Generation X. You can subscribe to receive their bi-weekly journal via 
email, write on their "wall for free thought", and use their list of 
links to find resources for knowledge and action.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.rnc.org"><font size=+2>Republican National 
Committee</font></a>
<dd><b>This site keeps you up-to-date on the latest happenings within 
the Republican Party.  You can participate in on-line discussions, 
download GOP-TV video clips, get Bob Dole's latest speeches, and  even 
visit the gift shop.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.democrats.org"><font size=+2>Democratic National 
Committee</font></a>
<dd><b>This site will give you up-to-the-minute news from the Democratic 
National Committee. It has information on the '96 Convention, Clinton 
Administration accomplishments, and you can sign up to receive press 
briefings and press releases via email.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.reformparty.org"><font size=+2>Reform Party</font></a>
<dd><b>Here you can find campaign updates, press releases, Ross Perot's 
speaking schedule, as well as other information from the Reform Party.</b>

<p> 

<dt><a href="http://www.lp.org/lp"><font size=+2>Libertarian Party</font></a>
<dd><b>This site gives you an overview of the philosophies and positions 
of the Libertarian Party. It also keeps you up to date on current activities 
within the party, gives you access to official Libertarian Party documents, 
and it gives you information on party membership as well.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.ustaxpayers.org"><font size=+2>U.S. Taxpayers 
Party</font></a>
<dd><b>This is the official U.S. Taxpayers Party Internet Headquarters. Here 
you can find their official platform, articles, speeches, late-breaking 
news, and you can even subscribe to their email notification service.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://sunsite.unc.edu:80/concord/cc_home.html"><font size=+2>The 
Concord Coalition</font></a>
<dd><b>This group is a non-partisan, grassroots movement that is trying to 
eliminate the deficit and bring entitlements down to a level which is fair 
to all generations. They have chapters in all 50 states. This site gives 
information about the Coalition and their materials, and it allows you to 
make contributions.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.pff.org"><font size=+2>The Progress &amp; Freedom 
Foundation</font></a>
<dd><b>This organization is devoted to restoring, renewing and recreating 
America's sense of its future, a future woven inextricably with the ideas 
of progress and freedom. This site contains many publications, information 
about the Foundation staff, and information about current projects.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.cc.org"><font size=+2>The Christian Coalition</font></a>
<dd><b>This organization, headed by Pat Robertson, has a web site that contains 
everything from press releases and voter's guides to Congressional scorecards 
which show how each state voted on various issues. This site also contains 
the <i>Christian American</i> magazine and allows you to subscribe to it 
online.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.townhall.com"><font size=+2>Town Hall</font></a>
<dd><b>The idea behind this organization is to bring internet users together 
with public policy organizations under the broad umbrella of 
&quot;conservative&quot; thoughts, ideas and actions. Thus, it contains 
many conservative public policy organizations, one of which is FRC. There 
are forums where you can post your comments, a store where you 
can purchase various materials, and weekly spotlights which focus on 
current issues. There is even a Job Bank for those of you who are 
looking for a job.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.heartland.org"><font size=+2>The Heartland 
Institute</font></a>
<dd><b>This is an 11-year old non-profit, non-partisan think tank that applies 
cutting-edge research to state and local public policy issues. Their 
research has been used by citizens across the country to cut taxes and 
reduce spending. This site contains most of their publications and allows you 
to sign up for &quot;membership&quot;.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.cei.org"><font size=+2>The Competitive Enterprise 
Institute</font></a>
<dd><b>This public policy group is committed to advancing the principles of 
free enterprise and limited government. Their site contains biographies of 
senior staff and an explanation of CEI. It contains many of their 
publications and allows you to subscribe to their E-Mail list or regular 
mailing list.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.gocin.com/afa/home.htm"><font size=+2>The American 
Family Association</font></a>
<dd><b>They stand for traditional family values, focusing primarily on the 
influence of television and other media - including pornography - on our 
society. This site contains an electronic edition of their monthly magazine, 
information about boycotts in progress, and information about their radio 
network. This site contains frames and looks best with 
<a href="http://home.netscape.com/comprod/mirror/index.html">Netscape 
2.0</a>.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.mcs.com/~dougp/stopftr.html"><font size=+2>Stop Fetal 
Tissue Research</font></a>
<dd><b>This non-profit organization is dedicated to reversing federal 
legislation legalizing human fetal tissue research and transplantation 
and human embryo research. This well-presented site contains many 
testimonies from people who survived abortions, or from people who were very 
premature and survived. They give reasons for their beliefs and  
they have many links to different pro-life and Christian sites. They 
also encourage people to contact their senators and congressmen and even 
the President in regard to various pieces of legislation.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.nrlc.org/"><font size=+2>National Right to Life 
Committee</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains information about who the NRLC is and what they do. 
It has an &quot;Action Alert&quot; which keeps you up to date on the latest 
abortion issues. There is a lot of information about partial-birth abortions, 
and the site contains all updates about federal legislation that 
deals with abortion. The top stories from <I>NRL News</i>, their daily 
newspaper, are also available.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.heritage.org"><font size=+2>The Heritage 
Foundation</font></a>
<dd><b>The Heritage Foundation is a research and educational institute whose 
mission is to formulate and promote conservative public policies based on the 
principles of free enterprise, limited government, individual freedom, 
traditional American values, and a strong national defense. This site 
contains everything from a Research Center and a Publications Library to 
commentaries from the president and &quot;Cyberpersonality Forums&quot;.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.townhall.com/conservative"><font size=+2>The 
American Conservative Union</font></a>
<dd><b>The American Conservative Union is the nation's oldest conservative 
lobbying organization. This site contains many of their publications and press 
releases, including ratings for the Congress. Also make sure to check out 
the &quot;Latest Republican Outrage&quot;.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.cwfa.org"><font size=+2>Concerned Women 
for America</font></a>
<dd><b>This is the nation's largest pro-family women's organization. Their 
site will keep you up to date on the organization as well as the issues 
that affect you and your family.</b>

</dl>

<p><hr size=3><p>

<a name="religious">
<center><b><font size=5><font size=6>R</font>ELIGIOUS 
<font size=6>L</font>INKS</font></b></center>

<p><dl>

<dt><a href="http://www.xir.com"><font size=+2>Christian Internet 
Resources</font></a>
<dd><b>From "International News" to a "Kid's Corner" to the "Christian 
Mystery Theater", this site contains all of the Christian Internet 
resources you could hope for, and more.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.gospelcom.net"><font size=+2>Gospel Communications 
Network</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains many different online Christian Resources. It has 
daily devotionals, many different Christian Organizations and their 
materials, and links to other Christian Resources. It even has a daily 
Christian cartoon called &quot;Reverend Fun&quot;.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.316csi.com/votd"><font size=+2>Verse 
of the Day E-Mail Subscription List</font></a>
<dd><b>Here you can sign up to a subscription list. Every day you will 
receive a Bible verse via E-Mail to brighten up your day.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.promisekeepers.org"><font size=+2>Promise 
Keepers Homepage</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains all kinds of information about this large men's 
movement. It includes the times and locations of upcoming conferences, 
the 7 promises of Promise Keepers, press releases, testimony from people 
who have attended, and even a "Prayer Room".</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.usa.net/~mmintl/mmi.html"><font size=+2>Marriage 
Ministries International</font></a>
<dd><b>This organization's goal is to see strong marriages and homes founded 
on Jesus Christ in every neighborhood in every nation before our Lord's return. 
This small site contains information about what they are and the course that 
they teach. It has names and numbers of people to contact across the U.S. 
and internationally for local ministry information.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.goshen.net/"><font size=+2>Goshen Christian 
Resource Directory</font></a>
<dd><b>The central goal of GOSHEN is to provide free access 
to Christian resources at an extensive, organized and 
searchable location on the World Wide Web. If you are looking for 
a particular Christian resource, it will most likely be listed here.</b> 

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.botcw.com/"><font size=+2>The Best 
of the Christian Web</font></a>
<dd><b>This site rates various Christian Web sites based on 3 different 
categories: usefulness, appearance and ease of use. The sites rated here 
are supposedly &quot;the best&quot; Christian web sites that the internet 
has to offer.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.students.uiuc.edu/~s-schim/christian/christian.html"><font size=+2>Christian Resources on the Web</font></a>
<dd><b>This site contains big lists of various Christian resources and sites on 
the internet. It is an excellent source of information.</b>

<p>

<dt><a href="http://www.ChristianAnswers.Net">
<font size=+2>ChristianAnswers.Net</font></a>
<dd><b>This site gives you biblical answers to important contemporary 
questions and issues, such as creation and evolution, religions and 
cults, family and marriage, etc. Are dinosaurs mentioned in the Bible? 
This site will tell you.</b>

</dl>

<p><HR SIZE = 3 WIDTH = 60%><p>

