<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Conservative Leadership Conference </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><B><STRONG>8th Annual Conservative Leadership Conference in Washington, D.C.</STRONG></B></FONT></CENTER></P>
</P><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>November 21-23, 1996</STRONG></FONT></CENTER></P>
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/lead-inst/alum.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER></P> "The education and training received at the Conservative Leadership Conference</P>
 is producing a new generation of conservative leaders."</P></CENTER>
<CENTER></P><B><STRONG>--Vice President Dan Quayle</STRONG></B></CENTER>
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/lead-inst/usflag.gif" ALT="Picture of US Flag"></CENTER>

</P><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><B><STRONG>Activists Wanted</STRONG></B></FONT></CENTER></P>
</P> In the old days there was another name for them.</P>
</P>
</P>Good Citizens</P>
</P>
</P>Individuals who understand their responsibility as Americans -- who believe in the defense of freedom passed down to us from the founding fathers.</P>
</P>
</P> A precious inheritance indeed.</P>
</P> Are you committed to conservative ideals? The ideals on which this country was founded?  The ideals which made this country great?</P>
</P> Of course you are. But  (and this is said gently) what are you doing about it?</P>
</P>
</P>Come to the 8th Annual Conservative Leadership Conference in Washington, D.C.</P>
</P>
<a name="register"></a>
</P> <HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2>
</P>
</P>
<big>Register for the 1996 Conservative Leadership Conference:</big><br>
Call Eric Putman, CLC Coordinator, at 1-800-827-5323<br> 
Or print out the following <a href="/lead-inst/clc.txt.html">form</a> and mail or fax it.

</P>
