<html>
<head>
<title>Footing the Bill</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<a href="/abic/top.map"><img src="/abic/images/top.gif" 
ALT="Americans Back in Charge Foundation" border="0" ISMAP></a>
<p><br>
<center><h2>Footing the Bill</h2></center>
<p><br>
<center>
<img src="/abic/images/ftb-7-29-96.gif" BORDER=0></a>
<p>
Source: <a href="http://www.ntu.org">National Taxpayers Union</a>
<p>

<p>
Earlier this month, the <a href="http://www.ntu.org">National Taxpayers Union</a> released a study of the cost of running House members' personal offices.  The figure above represents the entire total cost of all 435 offices.  
<p>
According to the press release which accompanied the release of the study, "the biggest office spender was former California Rep. Walter Tucker, who spent slightly more than he was legally allowed.  The most frugal office spender was Rep. Andy Jacobs (D-IN), who spent $265,124 less than the average representative.  If all members had spent as little as Rep. Jacobs, House office spending could have been slashed by 35%."  

<p>

<p>
<p align=center>
